[Desktop Entry]
# Managed by the desktop role (tasks/idle.yml). xss-lock runs the locker when the X
# screensaver activates, when logind requests a lock (loginctl lock-session), and before
# the system sleeps. It waits on the locker, so i3lock must not fork: hence -n.
#
# --notifier is what defers the locker to the screensaver's first cycle, giving the gap
# between the blank and lock timeouts that bspwm_idle.j2 programs. Without it xss-lock locks
# the moment the screen blanks. Nothing needs to be drawn during that gap, so the notifier
# is a no-op: it exits immediately and only its presence matters.
#
# -u drops the unlock indicator and -e ignores an empty password, leaving a screen that is
# nothing but desktop_i3lock_color.
Exec=/usr/bin/xss-lock --notifier=/bin/true -- /usr/bin/i3lock -n -u -e -c {{ desktop_i3lock_color }}
TryExec=/usr/bin/xss-lock
Name=xss-lock
Comment=Lock an idle X session
Type=Application
